cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on the practical aspects of training GANs, including regularization and normalization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GANs are often used in image generation tasks. The paper also discusses the use of neural architectures, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the reproducibility of GAN experiments, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.GR (Graphics).
